From f739502417c70c0eba73320df8d2dceca2a07051 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Scott <smb209@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Mar 2026 23:21:36 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Add container_name support to recipes

Introduce a container_name field to recipe schema and docs to allow running multiple recipes with distinct Docker container names (default: 'vllm_node'). Updates:

- recipes/README.md: Document container_name and guidance for running multiple recipes.
- run-recipe.py: Add schema field, default value, basic Docker-name validation (regex), import re, and logic to resolve/pass container_name into generated commands (only adds --name when not default). Also adjust dry-run output to show resolved container name.
- tests/test_recipes.sh: Add unit tests to verify default behavior (no --name emitted) and custom container_name is passed as --name.

This enables safer concurrent recipe runs by assigning unique container instance names and warns when a provided name may be invalid for Docker.
---
 recipes/README.md     |  5 ++++-
 run-recipe.py         | 32 +++++++++++++++++++++------
 tests/test_recipes.sh | 51 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-
 3 files changed, 79 insertions(+), 9 deletions(-)

diff --git a/recipes/README.md b/recipes/README.md
index 4f795ca..2247bb7 100644
--- a/recipes/README.md
+++ b/recipes/README.md
@@ -115,6 +115,8 @@ command: |
 # Optional fields
 description: What this recipe does
 model: org/model-name              # HuggingFace model ID for --setup downloads
+container_name: vllm_node          # Docker container instance name (default: vllm_node)
+                                   # Set a unique name to run multiple recipes simultaneously
 cluster_only: false                # Set to true if model requires cluster mode
 build_args:                        # Extra args for build-and-copy.sh
   - --pre-tf                       # e.g., for transformers 5.0
@@ -228,7 +230,8 @@ These arguments are appended to the end of the generated vLLM command after all
 3. Add `build_args` if your model needs special build options
 4. Add `mods` if your model needs patches
 5. Set `cluster_only: true` if model is too large for single node
-6. Set sensible `defaults`
+6. Set `container_name` if you want to run this recipe alongside another (e.g., `vllm-embedding`)
+7. Set sensible `defaults`
 7. Add `env` variables if needed
 
 Example:
diff --git a/run-recipe.py b/run-recipe.py
index ba4563b..b0a593c 100755
